5 It took some searching, but I finally discovered the finest sushi on the Northwest side of town. Yummy Sushi has one of the most knowledgeable sushi chefs around, and his dedication  to his craft is evident in every bite. They have the finest, freshest fish in town, often offering live shrimp and other crustations. The the chef is something of a marine biologist, giving patrons the lowdown on the spawning habits, migration and such of the various fish he serves.   Aside from the superior fish, the service is also top-notch with a welcoming, genuinely friendly athmosphere. It tends to get busy in the evenings, but definately worth the wait. It's also a bit pricier the the AYCE joints, the quality is unparalled. Simply the best sushi I've found.
5 Happened upon this place after a 12 hour day and needing to refuel before driving home and wasn't disappointed. The staff was incredibly friendly! I had the yellowtail sashimi and eel sashimi and both were excellent-and not  just because I hadn't eaten in eight hours. I can't remember what roll I had but it was delicious too and I pretty much embarrassed myself by eating my entire order in less than 10 minutes.  A lot of regulars came in during the time I was there which was a simple testament to the fact that this place has awesome food and great personalized service. It's a little out of the way for me, but I'd definitely go out of my way to come back!
4 I used to live minutes from the ocean and walking distance from amazing Omasake, so I wasn't sure I'd find similar caliber here in the desert of Las Vegas.  But, I am soooo glad that I gave "Yummy Grill & Sushi" a chance.  Don't let the fact that it is owned and staffed by non-Japanese fool you.  Nor the fact that it is in a strip mall in suberbia. They know sushi.    I have already been here twice in one week because the first time didn't fully satisfy my curiosity of their creative rolls from the extensive menu.  They are delicious, but The Kobe Beef Roll was OUTSTANDING.  I might make it 3 times this week, just so I can order that again.  The sushi and sashimi is impressively fresh.  Ama ebi is one of my favorite items, and it was fantastic, as was the perfectly deep fried head. Dipped in ponzu sauce...I was in heaven.   And the spicy tuna hand rolls are filling and so flavorful (it actually stands up to my favorite spicy tuna hand roll from Noshi Sushi!)   No doubt, I will be back again and again!
4 Wed afternoon, 3PM - Fantastic sushi and service.  Employee synergy was so good I had to ask the sushi chef (not the owner) whether or not it was a family owned restaurant.  My internal SushiBar™ was set by a once amazing Japanese sushi bar in Hollywood, a family run (in its heyday) bar I've frequented since I was a child.  Only today have I run into anything comparable.  Service was great - neither the chef nor server were overly talkative, but both were really pleasant, polite and attentive (I was waiting a moment as I'd ordered 2 of the most elaborate rolls I saw).  Despite my having ordered my sushi to-go, the chef served me a cucumber salad and the waitress brought water, which was kind.  I ordered three rolls, one of which was the Touchdown roll on the recommendation of an earlier reviewer - NICE!  I've forgotten the names of the other two rolls but, at the moment, I'm calling them all delicious.  The fish tasted fresh and I thought I could taste everything used in the rolls.  Impressive.
