3 Weren't feeling up to sushi so we grabbed some dinner specials.   Unagi Dinner ($13 comes with miso soup & salad)- pretty good, but it's a standard dish you know....most sushi places get their supply of pre cooked eel at the same place. Still, it's a "comfort" simple dish.  Tempura Dinner ($13 w/ miso &salad) - pretty good, crunchy. The portion was decent with 6 or so veggies, 5 shrimp and 1 crab stick. Crab stick was interesting to try since I've never seen that before- its A-OK and rather have an extra shrimp.   Miso is like any other miso soup, the salad had a good fresh dressing on it. The server also brought us a little pancake.   Now why 3 stars? So the star of the show seems to be sushi and quality sushi but someone at the sushi bar was a bit off putting and we were really glad that we didn't order raw fish that day from them. So one guy was counting money at the bar and later he started rubbing his head and scratching it vigorously. We then see him pick up knives and though he went to the sink to rinse off the knives....it's questionable if his hands hit soap. Just saying if you're counting money and scratching your pomade styled head your hand touching water isn't gonna cut it. I rarely get grossed out since I eat at some hole-in- the-walls that look like crack dens, but I see them wash their hands. The BF noticed it and he didn't like what he saw.   We would've come back for the creative sushi another time since we see all these rave reviews, but I think we might pass onto someplace else. Can't really give more than 3 stars to a place we probably wont return to.
