5 Yup, call Cheaters cause I cheated....I cheated on Goyemon...But like Smokey said, "Take a picture, write it down, I don't give a F@#K!!!" (from the movie FRIDAY, FYI)  The 2 Live Crew, I mean the THREE Live Crew made me do it!!!!!  1) LIVE Uni (Sea Urchin)  2) LIVE Mirugai (Giant Clam)  3) LIVE Amaebi (Sweet Shrimp)  MASSIVE MAHALOS to Kimberly T. for sharing the love!!!! We were planning on a dinner and a movie, but instead, we got an even better dinner and a show!!! Here's how it unfolded:  THE PREVIEW  We've been to the "Old" Yummy Grill and sushi where they offered Chinese, Local Style plate lunches, and lackluster sushi. Well, ever since The Chef/Owner Eric took over three years ago, he has been slowly phasing out that concept with an "Out with the old, in with the new" High End/Western-Style sushi Bar, catering to both the traditionalist, and one who is all about the rolls. A name change is also in the works... I called in ahead and got everything situated...  Me: "Hello, I'm calling in to see if you have fresh Amaebi tonight?" Jennifer: "Yes we do"......BIG SMILE! Me: "How about Live Uni?" Jennifer: "Yes we do".....EVEN BIGGER SMILE, MY CHEEKS ARE HURTING! Me: "We would like two for the bar...and what time do you close?" Jennifer: " 2am"  **Cheers from our end of the line, laughter from her end of the line**  INTRODUCTION  "Irrasshaimasse!" as we enter the door, Jennifer directs us to our reserved spot at the bar in front of Eric.He introduces himself, the other chefs Sam, and Jun-San, and Jennifer, who we spoke to earlier, he even introduces us to a regular at the bar! We introduce ourselves to them all, and while wifey looks through the menu, my eyes are glued to the Fresh Seafood board that changes on a daily basis based on what Eric can get in on that day. We order a live Uni, two Amaebi and a Crazy Jalapeno to start...  THE BUILD-UP  Some amuse-bouche action starts us off with some cucumber sunomono with krab and vegetable-tempura pancakes along with our Crazy Jalapeno. They were all okay, but I came here for the main attractions...Eric brings us our order of two ALIVE AND KICKING Amaebi, and everyone else at the bar is wondering what they are (everyone around us was grubbin' on rolls and yum-yum laced creations, no one even knew what the Uni was when Jun-San brought it out to show us before creating our uni masterpiece with sushi rice!(another option is to have it prepared with cold soba noodles) Eric and the rest of the staff are also so very passionate, personable, and very informative, and  another thing that Eric mentioned is where he gets most of his premium seafood from-Japan (Tsukiji and Kyushu), Spain, and Boston...Hmmmm, sound familiar??? You know for a fact that the specials board is the way to go if you take your sushi seriously. Service here is nothing short of top-notch, and it shows in everything Eric and his staff does.  THE ACTION  Our Amaebi course arrives in three parts-HUGE fried head, tail section with black tobiko, and tail end with yuzu tobiko with a citrus-soy dipping sauce. The tail is so sweet and meaty, and the head is so crunchy and delicious! It is so awesome to watch Eric and the other chefs do their thing with great attention to detail and the passion that is displayed with each piece of edible art they place in front of us. Jun-San hands us our live uni masterpiece, and we dig in to this ocean butta, savoring each and every tasty bite. Coincidentally, everyone at the bar were first timers at that moment, so it called for free sake on the house! The house was also VERY generous to us, with garlic edamame, salmon carpaccio, a bottle of housemade Soju Cocktail, and they weren't done yet! Eric showed us pictures of his fresh fish selections and brought out a huge head of a Kinmedai (Alfonsino) from Tsukiji Market in Japan which was later presented to us grilled! (Ji-Kinmedai Kama) Loved that meaty, fatty goodness! The eyeballs were bomb.com too!  THE CLIMAX  We ended our dinner with an order each of Kohada (Spotted Sardine, AKA Gizzard Shad) and Mirugai (Giant Clam, AKA Geoduck) Eric brought out the Geoduck before cutting it, and then the ding-a-ling jokes came out between Eric and another guy that had everyone rolling!(See Photos) They were both sooo ONOLICIOUS!!! Oh yeah, one order here is TWO pieces...The "other place" is just one...how's that???  THE END/SNEAK PEAK  Two and a half hours later, after a great dinner(& show) and talking story throughout the night with everyone just having such a good time, we payed our bill, thanked everyone at Yummy Grill, and seeing our appreciation for "The Good Stuff", Eric capped our night off with an order of melt-in-your-mouth Shima-Aji (Striped Jack) topped with sea kelp and fresh wasabi...What a first-time experience this was, and most definitely won't be our last....ALOHA!!!!  YELP 365 CHALLENGE-(289/365) "Me So Hungry, Me Love You LONG Time!"
5 In a city where mediocre all you can eat sushi places serve forgettable bites of fish, its refreshing to see a place that actually knows and cares about the type and quality of fish they serve.  The plethora of fresh fish that you normally would not see at a sushi bar off the strip was amazing.  The live amaebi, live scallops, and fresh octopus was a delightful experience.  For sushi connoisseurs that appreciate quality nigiri over rolls covered in sauce, i really recommend the kinmedai and the kohada here. It reminded me of my years in Tokyo eating at Tsukiji.  Unfortunately they did not have blue fin tuna in stock because the quality was not up to their standards.  Just to hear that they send back sub standard fish is refreshing to hear.  Too many times have i seen awful qualities of fish being served to other patrons at other sushi bars.  I will definately return to taste the blue fin.  If you want a quality sushi experience I highly recommend Yummy Grill Sushi.
